    "body": "Actually, looks like we do support not only nodejs v10 but also v8. I was convinced that we removed the jobs running on older versions from solc-js but just noticed that [we did not](https://github.com/ethereum/solc-js/blob/v0.8.10/.circleci/config.yml#L5-L10). So we apparently still test solc-js on the whole v8-v16 range and even have jobs for v4 and v6 (I suspect that they won't pass though).\r\n\r\nEDIT: Yeah, I checked just for fun and no v4 or v6: `ReferenceError: WebAssembly is not defined`. So these are definitely unsupported :)",
